President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Steven Anthony is nominated for Member of the Railroad Retirement Board. He has previously served as Senior General Counsel and Secretary for the Norfolk Southern Corporation. Susan McCue is nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation. She is currently the President of Message Global and has previously served as Chief of Staff for U.S. Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid. Deb Miller is nominated for Member of the Surface Transportation Board. She is currently a Senior Associate for Cambridge Systematics, Inc. and has previously served as Secretary of the Kansas Department of Transportation. Catherine Ann Novelli is nominated for Under Secretary for Economic Growth, Energy, and the Environment at the Department of State. She is currently the Vice President of Worldwide Government Affairs at Apple, Inc. and has previously served at the Office of the United States Trade Representative.